{"id":"u1-2-soft-pronunciation","day":"1.2 — 2. den","title":"Soft pronunciations: ť, ď, ň and ě","summary":"Read the spelling patterns that signal soft consonants and j-like sounds.","estimatedMinutes":20,"objectives":["Recognize ť, ď, and ň before ordinary vowels","Interpret d/t/n before i, í, and ě as soft","Read p/b/v/m + ě patterns","Connect the spellings with pictures and spoken Czech"],"sections":[{"heading":"Written ť, ď, ň","body":"Before a, o, u, or at the end of a word, the soft consonants are written with a háček.","examples":["koťata","Maďarsko","píseň"]},{"heading":"Before i, í, and ě","body":"The háček is not written on d, t, or n before i, í, or ě; these spellings signal the soft pronunciations ď, ť, and ň.","examples":["tělo","studenti","dělat","kamarádi","něco","nic"]},{"heading":"p, b, v, m + ě","body":"Before ě, p, b, and v are pronounced with a following j sound. The sequence mě is pronounced approximately mně.","examples":["pěna ≈ pjena","běhat ≈ bjehat","Věra ≈ Vjera","město ≈ mněsto"]}],"vocabulary":[{"czech":"tělo","english":"body","note":"t + ě signals soft ť."},{"czech":"dělat","english":"to do","note":"d + ě signals soft ď."},{"czech":"něco","english":"something","note":"n + ě signals soft ň."},{"czech":"město","english":"city","note":"mě is pronounced approximately mně."},{"czech":"píseň","english":"song","note":"Final ň is written with háček."}],"transcript":[],"resources":[{"title":"Original lesson: Soft Pronunciations","kind":"Reality Czech lesson","url":"https://realityczech.org/soft-pronunciations/","note":"Source for ť/ď/ň and ě spelling patterns and detailed image attributions."},{"title":"koťata","kind":"pronunciation image","url":"https://realityczech.org/wp-content/uploads/gdoc/google-2517-1.png","note":"kittens"},{"title":"ťuknout","kind":"pronunciation image","url":"https://realityczech.org/wp-content/uploads/gdoc/google-2517-2.png","note":"to tap"},{"title":"Maďarsko","kind":"pronunciation image","url":"https://realityczech.org/wp-content/uploads/gdoc/google-2517-3.png","note":"Hungary"},{"title":"Vláďovi","kind":"pronunciation image","url":"https://realityczech.org/wp-content/uploads/gdoc/google-2517-4.png","note":"to Vláďa"},{"title":"koňak","kind":"pronunciation image","url":"https://realityczech.org/wp-content/uploads/gdoc/google-2517-5.jpg","note":"cognac"},{"title":"píseň","kind":"pronunciation image","url":"https://realityczech.org/wp-content/uploads/gdoc/google-2517-6.png","note":"song"},{"title":"tělo","kind":"pronunciation image","url":"https://realityczech.org/wp-content/uploads/gdoc/google-2517-7.png","note":"body"},{"title":"studenti","kind":"pronunciation image","url":"https://realityczech.org/wp-content/uploads/gdoc/google-2517-8.png","note":"students"},{"title":"dělat","kind":"pronunciation image","url":"https://realityczech.org/wp-content/uploads/gdoc/google-2517-9.png","note":"to do"},{"title":"kamarádi","kind":"pronunciation image","url":"https://realityczech.org/wp-content/uploads/gdoc/google-2517-10.png","note":"friends"},{"title":"něco","kind":"pronunciation image","url":"https://realityczech.org/wp-content/uploads/gdoc/google-2517-11.png","note":"something"},{"title":"nic","kind":"pronunciation image","url":"https://realityczech.org/wp-content/uploads/gdoc/google-2517-12.png","note":"nothing"},{"title":"pěna","kind":"pronunciation image","url":"https://realityczech.org/wp-content/uploads/gdoc/google-2517-13.png","note":"foam"},{"title":"běhat","kind":"pronunciation image","url":"https://realityczech.org/wp-content/uploads/gdoc/google-2517-14.png","note":"to run"},{"title":"Věra","kind":"pronunciation image","url":"https://realityczech.org/wp-content/uploads/gdoc/google-2517-15.png","note":"Vera"},{"title":"město","kind":"pronunciation image","url":"https://realityczech.org/wp-content/uploads/gdoc/google-2517-16.png","note":"city"}],"exercises":[{"type":"multiple_choice","prompt":"How is the initial consonant in tělo pronounced?","choices":["Like ordinary t","Like soft ť","Like c","It is silent"],"correctIndex":1,"explanation":"Before ě, written t signals the soft consonant ť."},{"type":"text_entry","prompt":"Type the Czech word for “city.”","acceptedAnswers":["město"],"explanation":"The word is město; the sequence mě is pronounced approximately mně."},{"type":"multiple_choice","prompt":"Which spelling is pronounced approximately “Vjera”?","choices":["Vera","Věra","Fěra","Vjera"],"correctIndex":1,"explanation":"v + ě produces a j-like glide."}],"sourceUrl":"https://realityczech.org/soft-pronunciations/","sourceAttribution":"Reality Czech, Christian Hilchey, COERLL","contentLicense":"CC BY-SA"}
